}

[quote author=Vira_ link=topic=381133.msg2864235#msg2864235 date=1247357029]
A single Java method cannot compile to more than 64KB of byte code. As Clover adds statements to record code coverage to every statement in your source file, a method which is close to this limit may exceed it when instrumented. The solution at present is:

  1. As a work-around, split your method into two smaller ones.
    [/quote][/quote]
